For all aspects of the cooling experiment, the simulations were performed as in refs. 9–11. The only new aspect of the simulation is the treatment of the atom recoil due to photon absorption and emission, which was implemented for the cooling/heating phase of the experiment as well as the probing phase. As with the simulation of Lyman-α absorption10,11, the probability for photon absorption is determined from the Doppler-shifted absorption profile, which includes the laser intensity at the position of the antihydrogen atom when a laser pulse occurs. At each time step, the occurrence of an absorption event is determined by generating a random number and comparing it with the calculated probability. If the absorption occurs, the antihydrogen velocity is changed by vreck^\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
